subSubSection.paragraph:
This species is similar to 
Heterospilus cushmani
but differs by having the stigma bicolored (entirely brown in 
Heterospilus cushmani
), the hind coxa and femur dark brown (yellow or very light brown in 
Heterospilus cushmani
), and the mesoscutal lobes granulate but rugose along the notauli (entirely granulate in 
Heterospilus cushmani
).
